:::summary
The Doctrine and Covenants (D&C) is a collection of divine revelations and inspired declarations received primarily by the Prophet Joseph Smith. It serves as a unique volume of scripture in that — unlike the Bible or Book of Mormon — it addresses the restored Church directly in the modern era, covering everything from church organization and priesthood to cosmic theology and the afterlife. It is one of the four standard works of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.
:::

